The shadow of the Renaissance | La sombra del Renacimiento #nicanorgarcia #travelarchitectures ⠀
The calmest place at the Ponte Vecchio isn’t around the jewelry shops or in the Vasari corridor, it’s under the bridge and I shot it with my #HuaweiP20Pro. Awesome weekend in Florence touring with the winners of the challenge the works of the Medici, Brunelleschi, Michelangelo, Vasari, Botticelli... among others, that sparked the Renaissance. Thank you @huaweimobileesp for #sparkarenaissance

Industrial diamond | Diamante industrial #nicanorgarcia #travelarchitectures
The Bauhaus school existed for a total of 14 years. During 7 of those years, it was located in Dessau, where Walter Gropius moved it from Weimar. Its influence on industrial and graphic design, architecture, photography, typography and other applied arts is immense even today after 100 years since its birth.
In my case it influenced me not only during my studies of architecture, but also while I was a professor of architecture and I designed my buildings as an architect. I would say that it still greatly affects my photography.
If you think about it, I’m sure it influenced you too. Congratulations Bauhaus!
